@startuml
' Purpose: Core Data Model - Reference examples
' Source of truth:
'   src/api/schemas/journey.ts
'   src/api/schemas/forms.ts
'   src/api/schemas/case.ts
'   src/api/service/researchConsents.ts

title Core Data Model - Reference

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho

legend top
  | Notation | Meaning |
  | field? | Optional/nullable field |
  | field[] | Array/list field |
  | *Id | Identifier reference field |
  | YYYY-MM-DD | Anchor date |
  | ISO datetime | Persisted timestamp |
endlegend

note as JourneyTemplateRef
JourneyTemplate
- parentTemplateId?: lineage to parent template
- derivedAt?: last parent sync timestamp
- referenceDateLabel: visible assignment anchor label
end note

note as JourneyEntryRef
JourneyTemplateEntry
- offsetDays + windowDays drive due windows
- scoreAliases maps raw score keys to stable policy aliases
- recurrenceIntervalDays enables recurring occurrences
end note

note as FormResponseRef
FormResponse
- patientJourneyId?: runtime journey context
- journeyTemplateEntryId?: originating template entry
- occurrenceIndex?: recurring instance index
end note

note as ConsentRef
Consent
- grantedAt / grantedByUserId always set on grant
- revokedAt / revokedByUserId set on revoke
- one active consent per patient+module+journey
- revoked records are retained for audit history
end note

note as InstructionRef
Instruction
- startDayOffset/endDayOffset stored from template
- startAt/endAt persisted and shifted on journey resume
- status: ACTIVE -> ACKNOWLEDGED -> COMPLETED or CANCELLED
end note

JourneyTemplateRef .. JourneyEntryRef
JourneyEntryRef .. FormResponseRef
FormResponseRef .. InstructionRef
InstructionRef .. ConsentRef

@enduml
